> In this recipe, we've given one of our customer favourites, honey roasted sausages, an Italian-inspired
> makeover by turning them into meatballs! Rolled into balls, and mixed together with a delicious
> red onion relish and panko breadcrumbs (which holds them together) these meatballs are a great
> thing to cook with the kids over a lazy weekend. Combined with a veg packed sauce, and finished
> off with a good sprinkling of chopped parsley, we've covered all bases when it comes to getting
> fussy eaters on your side! Fast family food at its finest!

== Meatballs ==

Slice open the @British Honey Mustard Sausages{4}, remove the meat and discard the skin.
Place the sausage meat in a #mixing bowl{} and add the @caramelized red onion relish{20%g}
and @panko breadcrumbs{30%g}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.
Mix thoroughly with your hands, then form into four meatballs per person. Set aside
on a #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

== Rice ==

Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #large saucepan{} and bring to the boil.
When boiling, add and dissolve half the @chicken stock powder{1/2}, then stir in the
@Basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Cook
for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for
another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

> TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

== Sauce and Finishing ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium heat. When hot,
add the meatballs and fry until browned all over, turning occasionally,
~{5-6%minutes}. Remove to a plate (keep the pan!)

> TIP: Do this in batches to brown rather than stew the meatballs!

> TIP: Don't worry about the meatballs being cooked all the way through at this point,
> we will finish them off in the sauce later.

While the meatballs brown, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds.
Chop into small pieces. When the meatballs are out of the pan, add the pepper and
cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @mangetout{150%g}, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{150%g},
@water for the sauce{100%ml} and remaining chicken stock powder. Bring to the boil,
stirring to dissolve the stock powder, then lower the heat to medium. Return the
meatballs to the sauce. Simmer until they are cooked through, ~{7-9%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).
Stir half through the sauce. Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed. Fluff up
the rice with a #fork{} and divide between your plates. Top with the meatballs and
sauce and finish with a sprinkling of remaining parsley. Enjoy!